reviews.review:
This is probably the most underrated game ever. If you compare it to Oblivion, then yeah.. it's not even close, but it's a very good game anyway. 

Pros:
 - Tons of item, especially Armor and Weapons. You can call yourself a hero if you manage to collect 10+ full sets through the game;
 - Stacking items of same class; 
 - Very organized inventory;
 - Beautiful graphics and places; 
 - Cool spells;
 - Traps and bombs. 

Cons: 
 - Shallow storyline. And that hot girl is your SISTER... WTF!?; 
 - Dumb conversations (but still funny); 
 - Not the most attractive combat sistem; 
 - You become overpower fairly soon, but still there are monsters which will kill you with one hit. 

Overall it's a good game and you will like it if you are not expecting something like Oblivion. It's more like Gothic 3, but better optimized and more beautiful. If it's on discount it's a must-have game.

There is a sequel too and it's one hell of a game. Actually one of my 10/10 games.
